article.headline: S. Illinois 73, Chicago St. 57
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- Diamond Taylor scored 19 points and Mamadou Seck added 16 points and 10 rebounds to lead Chicago State to a 73-57 victory against Chicago State on Friday night. Josh Swan scored 11 points and Jeff Early 10 for the Salukis (1-3). Matt Samuels and Jeremy Robinson scored 15 points each for the Cougars (0-5). Robinson had nine rebounds. Early scored six points during an 8-0 run over a stretch of 4:20 in the second half. His jumper with 13:26 remaining gave Southern Illinois a 44-28 lead, and Chicago State got no closer than nine points the rest of the way.
